{"id": 14436, "date": "1987-03-13T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-03-13T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=14436"}, "modified": "2026-06-09T17:04:34", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-10T00:04:34", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-and-beaver-brown-money-thats-what-i-want", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/03/13/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-beaver-brown-money-thats-what-i-want/", "title": {"rendered": "Money (That&#8217;s What I Want)"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Barrett Strong&#8217;s original 1959 recording of &#8220;Money (That&#8217;s What I Want)&#8221; ushered in the age of Motown as a cultural force.\u00a0Peaking at #2 on the Billboard R&amp;B chart and #23 on the Hot 100, &#8220;Money&#8221; was Motown&#8217;s first of many hit singles.</p>\n<p>If the original recording below sounds a bit loose, that&#8217;s because it was: &#8220;Money&#8221; was the result of an improvisational recording session&#8211;so improvisational in fact, that the guitarist and bassist remained unknown for years, because they were high school amateurs who happened to be passing by the studio at the right time.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/t5KU34DrrPI?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Just a few years later, of course, The Beatles would cover Strong&#8217;s hit single, bringing the song to an even wider audience.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/CeWjEYhk7Xo?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>The Beatles&#8217; version is probably the one that first captured Bruce&#8217;s attention; his high school band The Castiles began covering it in 1965, barely a year after the song appeared on\u00a0<em>With the Beatles.</em></p>\n<p>We know The Castiles covered it thanks to surviving set list documents, but unfortunately there are no surviving recordings. (It&#8217;s amazing that anything survives from the Castiles era at all. Who could have predicted Bruce&#8217;s rise to fame back then?)</p>\n<p>In fact, even though Bruce has covered &#8220;Money (That&#8217;s What I Want)&#8221; at least a half-dozen times over the years, it&#8217;s maddeningly difficult to track down audio evidence of it, since none of those times were during an &#8220;official&#8221; concert, E Street or otherwise.</p>\n<p>But we do have two vintage recordings of Bruce covering this R&amp;B classic, both dating back to surprise Jersey shore club appearances in the 1980s.</p>\n<p>The first was with Beaver Brown at the short-lived Big Man&#8217;s West in February 1982. The recording is muddy, but it&#8217;s clear enough to tell just how hot a performance it was on what must have been a very cold night:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/6izI6xtDOf8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>The next time Bruce covered &#8220;Money&#8221; was more than five years later&#8211;this time at The Stone Pony in Asbury Park in the summer of 1987, during a rare full E Street Band appearance (almost, anyway&#8211;Nils wasn&#8217;t there that night) at the legendary club. This one&#8217;s a bit clearer:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Wx8xeRbYNUA?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>Updated 1/7/2021: </strong>Bruce has played &#8220;Money (That&#8217;s What I Want)&#8221; a couple of times since, but you&#8217;d have had to be fortunate, connected or wealthy enough to attend the private benefit shows where he performed them, like this 2016 benefit for the U.S. Equestrian Team.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/e6n2jeN_x7E?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>The rest of us will have to be content with these rare club recordings from the eighties.</p>\n<p><strong>Money (That&#8217;s What I Want)<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> February 20, 1982 (Red Bank, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> January 22, 2016 (Wellington, FL)</p>\n<p>November 26, 2019</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce Springsteen has covered Motown&#8217;s first big hit several times over the years, but only two club performances from the eighties were caught on tape. Take a listen to both inside.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69812, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false}, "categories": [4, 3617, 5], "tags": [2560, 330, 2559, 238], "class_list": ["post-14436", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-it-takes-two", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-barrett-strong", "tag-beaver-brown", "tag-money-thats-what-i-want", "tag-the-beatles"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/admin-ajax-2026-06-09T170231.767.jpg?fit=1000%2C1000&ssl=1", "jetpack_sh